rlSubFrameCfg_t::subFramePeriodicity
rlUInt32_t subFramePeriodicity
subFramePeriodicity >= Sum total time of all bursts + InterSubFrameBlankTime, Where, Sum total time of all bursts = numOfBurstLoops * numOfBurst * burstPeriodicity. InterSubFrameBlankTime is primarily for sensor calibration / monitoring, thermal control, transferring out any safety monitoring data if requested, hardware reconfiguration for next sub frame, retriggering of next SF (~10us). The hardware reconfiguration time, which is needed to transfer out the SF's InterSubFrameBlankTime >= 100 us. With loopback enabled InterSubFrameBlankTime >= 350 us. Add 150 us to InterSubFrameBlankTime for test source confguration if test source is enabled. 1 LSB = 5 ns Valid range 100 us to 1.342 s.
